Motorola Inc expects continuedsteady improvement in semiconductor orders for the rest of theyear, Executive Vice President and Chief Corporate StaffOfficer Gary Tooker told security analysts.    He said the company's semiconductor products sector showeda nine pct increase in sales last year to 1.88 billion dlrs andexpects growth this year to range between 11 and 13 pct.    Semiconductor products accounted for 31 pct of Motorola's1986 net sales of 5.89 billion dlrs.    Tooker said Motorola has shipped about 300,000 of its32-bit 68020 microprocessor to 200 customers. Apple ComputerInc recently announced it is using the 68020 in its new Mac IIpersonal computer. Reuter&#3;